Implementation Plan
#Snapshot / Backup (Performed by ACN Midrange Windows)
Log in to the vCenter/vSphere Management Console.

Locate the target VMs.

Initiate the "Create Snapshot" process.

Include the Change Request (CR) number in the Description for tracking.

Verify that the snapshot task has reached "Completed" status.

#VMware Action (Performed by ACN Midrange Windows)
Navigate to the "Actions" menu.

Select "Edit Settings."

Click on "Add New Device" and select "Hard Disk."

Specify the required disk capacity in GB.

Confirm the hardware configuration change.

#Windows Action (Performed by ACN Midrange Windows)
Access the target servers via CyberArk.

Launch "Computer Management" via Windows search.

Navigate to "Disk Management."

Locate the new disk, right-click, and select "Initialize Disk."

Select "GPT (GUID Partition Table)" as the partition style.

Define the partition size as requested.

Format the volume using the naming convention: servername_unitname_NTFS.

Capture a screenshot of the new disk configuration as evidence.

#Communicate completion (Performed by ACN Midrange Windows)
Notify the requester via Microsoft Teams and email once the implementation is finalized.

Test Plan
#Technical Test (Performed by ACN Midrange Windows)
Access the newly created partition.

Perform a read/write test by creating, copying, and deleting a test file to ensure volume stability.

Backout Plan
#Remove the Disk (Performed by ACN Midrange Windows)
Log in to the vCenter/vSphere Management Console.

Locate the VMs and access "Edit Settings."

Identify and remove the newly added hard disk from the hardware list.

#Snapshot Rollback (Performed by ACN Midrange Windows)
If the server becomes unstable, log in to vCenter.

Locate the VM and perform a "Revert to Snapshot" using the backup created prior to the change.
